
### 2. `.gitignore`

This file ensures that certain files (like environment configurations and dependencies) are not tracked by Git.

**Sample content for `.gitignore`:**

```bash
# Python files
*.py[cod]
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd

# Virtual environment
venv/
.env

# Migrations
migrations/

# Flask/Django-specific files
instance/
*.log

# Database
*.sqlite3
*.db

# OS-specific files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
